{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"19b56b47-3c2c-411c-a595-de51c40afcb9","content":"The project uses **MSTest v3.8.0** with the new Microsoft Testing Platform (`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport=true`). Tests are categorized with `[TestCategory]` — I'll filter for \"Integration\".","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Y2dpPT42pR39oJLJobsjVp","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Running integration tests"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_0145rZBdwHa6JZbo2WVkZgp8","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/sv-b13428fec36044f4bcec7ac86f80f5f8 && dotnet test --filter \"TestCategory=Integration\" 2>&1","description":"Run MSTest integration tests","initial_wait":60},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Run MSTest integration tests"}],"interactionId":"38c3f834-4995-411c-9edc-7d644ff26526","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project uses **MSTest** (v3.8.0) as the test framework. The tests are categorized with `[TestCategory]` attributes — \"Unit\" and \"Integration\". The user wants to run only the integration tests.\n\nThe `Directory.Build.props` enables `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`, which means this uses the newer Microsoft Testing Platform (not the older VSTest runner). With MSTest v3+ and this property, `dotnet test` uses the new testing platform.\n\nTo filter for integration tests, I need to use the appropriate filter. With MSTest and `dotnet test`, I can use `--filter \"TestCategory=Integration\"`.\n\n\nNow I'll execute the command to run just the integration tests.","outputTokens":397,"requestId":"4816:2AD648:8A0751:9EC602:69FBEBC3"},"id":"e5feddb7-2e44-4ea3-b6bb-b863a388950a","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:32:59.595Z","parentId":"67ab299a-3da2-4119-87b6-9b5cab071f3d"}
